50|$|IPEX, the InterParliamentary EU {{information}} eXchange, is {{a platform}} for the exchange of information between EU national parliaments {{as well as the}} European Parliament concerning issues related to the European Union, {{especially in light of the}} provisions of the Treaty of Lisbon. The Treaty of Lisbon explicitly sets out the role of the national parliaments in the Protocol on the role of national Parliaments in the European Union and in the Protocol on the application <b>of</b> the <b>principles</b> <b>of</b> <b>subsidiarity</b> and proportionality.|$|R
